The paper deals with generating facial attributes using a 3D representation, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) techniques. The proposed method involves the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs), which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Finally, the experiments involve image and video processing (cs.MM) datasets and evaluation metrics.
